sec.p:
Bayesian Poisson regression models were used to assess associations with the number of monthly cases in 199 sub-districts. Population was used as the denominator in the model (i.e. log-population as an offset). The neighborhood relationship between the sub-districts were defined using their adjacency matrix; ‘1’ for a pair of sub-districts sharing a border, otherwise ‘0’. Hence the following model was used:
